Files:
- plugins/notion/src/notion-api.ts (replace localStorage iteration, lines 55-70)

Context:
Current code (lines 53-71):
  try {
    // Scan localStorage for spaceId patterns
    for (let i = 0; i < localStorage.length; i++) {
      const key = localStorage.key(i);
      if (key?.includes('spaceId')) {
        const val = getLocalStorage(key);
        if (val) {
          try {
            const parsed = JSON.parse(val) as { value?: string };
            if (parsed.value?.match(/^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-/)) {
              return parsed.value;
            }
          } catch {
            if (val.match(/^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-/)) return val;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  } catch {}

The SDK's findLocalStorageEntry(predicate) iterates localStorage keys safely and returns the first entry where predicate returns true. Use it:
  const entry = findLocalStorageEntry(key => key.includes('spaceId'));
  if (entry) {
    try {
      const parsed = JSON.parse(entry.value) as { value?: string };
      if (parsed.value?.match(/^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-/)) return parsed.value;
    } catch {
      if (entry.value.match(/^[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-/)) return entry.value;
    }
  }

Note: findLocalStorageEntry only returns the FIRST matching entry. If the existing behavior iterates ALL matching entries (checking each for the UUID pattern), you may need to handle the case where the first 'spaceId' key doesn't have a UUID-formatted value. In that case, you cannot directly replace the loop with a single findLocalStorageEntry call — you'd need to iterate all matching entries. Check whether there is typically only one spaceId entry in Notion's localStorage or multiple.

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the first try-catch block that reads 'LRU:KeyValueStore2:lastVisitedRouteSpaceId' (lines 43-50) — keep that as is
- Do NOT change the UUID regex pattern
- findLocalStorageEntry is exported from '@opentabs-dev/plugin-sdk' — add it to the import if not present
